    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`autocomplete` menu doesn't show in some cases even when completion items do exist.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5fbf0d44-0320-4666-b357-b6bfcd5c5c4e)\n\nObserve that the completion item doesn't show up, until I escape and re-enter insert mode (after typing `.c`). I could have also done `C-x C-o`\n\nThis doesn't happen everywhere, but the place I have noticed this happening every time is reproduced in 'Steps to reproduce' section.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate a file `config.lua` with following content:\n\n```lua\nvim.pack.add({ \"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\" })\nvim.lsp.enable({ \"emmet_language_server\" })\nvim.o.autocomplete = true\nvim.o.completeopt = 'menu,menuone,noinsert'\nvim.o.complete = 'o'\n```\n\n`$ nvim -u config.lua`\n\n`:e test.html`\n\nEnter insert mode and type `.`, you will see autocomplete menu popup with one entry.\n\nType some random character, like `.c` and the autocomplete menu becomes invisible even when a completion item exists.\n\nIt can be confirmed that the completion item exists by either doing `C-x C-o` or by escaping and re-entering insert mode (`<esc>a`)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe autocomplete menu shouldn't become invisible when completion items do exist.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2583+g0ca9849387\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim doesn't have `autocomplete`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.26.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo",
